<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="vs-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">TL;DR</p>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="vs-tldr-body">For most US small businesses with payroll, QuickBooks Online wins on ecosystem; Xero wins on price and multi-entity bookkeeping. Past $25M or multi-location inventory, both lose to mid-market systems.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="vs-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Which is cheaper, QuickBooks Online or Xero?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Xero starts lower ($20 vs $35/mo) and stays lower at comparable tiers.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Which handles US payroll better?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">QuickBooks — payroll is native; Xero relies on a third-party integration (Gusto).</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Is switching between them hard?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">A standard migration runs 2–4 weeks including historical data; we publish fixed migration pricing.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Which do accountants prefer?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">In the US, QuickBooks — the ProAdvisor network is far larger, which matters when you need help fast.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What does TechBrot recommend?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Whichever fits your profile — we hold no reseller incentives in either direction.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

